sec.p:
Among them,
PConv(·)
 indicates partial convolution; 
W1,W2∈ℝCr×2Cr
 is channel-by-channel linear mapping; 
GELU(·)
 is the gaussian error linear units; 
Splitchan(·)
 represents the operation of dividing into two equal parts according to the channel dimension; 
R(·),F(·)
 reform and flattening operations that represent mutual transformation between sequences and two-dimensional space; 
DWConv(·)
 indicates channel-wise separable convolution; 
⊗
 represents matrix multiplication between channels; 
X^1⊗F(·)
 responsible for simplifying redundant dimensions by channel.
